Horace's noblest3 its national characteristics are well summed up by Andrew Lang in his Letters to Dead Autlmrs, p. 191 f. ‘None but a patriot could have sung that ode on Regulus, who died, as our hero died on an evil day, for the honor of Rome, as Gordon for the honor of England. . . .
